WEBVTT

1
00:01:07.026 --> 00:01:08.611
<i>SUSAN: And that's the news.</i>

2
00:01:08.694 --> 00:01:13.699
But before we sign off, we'd like to
congratulate our very own Evan Baxter,

3
00:01:13.783 --> 00:01:17.578
who has just been elected
Buffalo's representative to Congress.

4
00:01:17.662 --> 00:01:20.081
- And, now, we have a surprise for Evan.
- No, you don't.

5
00:01:20.164 --> 00:01:23.542
- We do.
- Oh, no. I really didn't expect this.

6
00:01:23.626 --> 00:01:26.170
Here's a look back at his run for office.

7
00:01:26.254 --> 00:01:27.672
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

8
00:01:28.422 --> 00:01:31.259
<i>- What are we gonna do?
- ALL: Change the world!</i>

9
00:01:31.342 --> 00:01:32.343
<i>That's right!</i>

10
00:01:32.969 --> 00:01:34.470
<i>(ALL CHEERING)</i>

11
00:01:39.517 --> 00:01:41.560
<i>ALL: Baxter! Baxter! Baxter!</i>

12
00:01:48.526 --> 00:01:49.527
<i>Hi.</i>

13
00:01:49.610 --> 00:01:50.945
<i>ALL: Baxter! Baxter!</i>

14
00:01:51.028 --> 00:01:52.488
<i>That's right!</i>

15
00:01:54.740 --> 00:01:55.741
(CLEARING THROAT)

16
00:01:56.993 --> 00:02:01.205
I feel like that old Indian
in front of all the garbage.

17
00:02:02.707 --> 00:02:07.712
So, for the last time, this is Evan Baxter
for Eyewitness News. Good night.

18
00:02:08.462 --> 00:02:11.048
<i>(HAVE YOU EVER SEEN THE RAIN</i> PLAYING)

19
00:02:24.270 --> 00:02:27.481
<i>GPS: Huntsville, Virginia.
Prestige Crest, four miles.</i>

20
00:02:27.565 --> 00:02:30.192
- What did we do before GPS?
- Nothing.

21
00:02:30.276 --> 00:02:32.486
Guys, Dad's very proud of his new car.

22
00:02:32.570 --> 00:02:37.158
Hey, I am proud of my new car.
Look, I'm a politician now.

23
00:02:37.241 --> 00:02:40.161
I'm in the public eye, and as you know,
when you are in the public eye,

24
00:02:40.244 --> 00:02:41.912
image is everything, isn't it?

25
00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:49.295
EVAN: Here it is! Welcome to the good life.

26
00:02:49.837 --> 00:02:53.591
Hey, guys, why the long faces?
We're off on a new adventure!

27
00:02:54.216 --> 00:02:56.344
It's just we're going to miss our friends.

28
00:02:56.427 --> 00:02:58.262
You'll make new friends, better friends.

29
00:02:58.346 --> 00:02:59.513
Yeah, richer friends.

30
00:02:59.597 --> 00:03:03.351
Do not mouth off to me, sir.
I am the boss of you.

31
00:03:03.434 --> 00:03:05.770
And let me tell you something,
you guys are gonna love this place.

32
00:03:06.896 --> 00:03:09.648
And you know what? I think there's
something for our fishermen up there.

33
00:03:11.025 --> 00:03:13.944
EVAN: Baxter family,
this is what's called a scenic vista.

34
00:03:14.070 --> 00:03:18.032
And I don't think the big man himself
could do a better job. Pretty cool, huh?

35
00:03:18.115 --> 00:03:19.742
Hey, Dad, an iguana can stay underwater

36
00:03:19.825 --> 00:03:20.910
- for 28 minutes.
- What's that?

37
00:03:20.993 --> 00:03:22.870
- And a shrimp's heart is in its head.
- Really?

38
00:03:22.953 --> 00:03:25.206
Okay, someone's had enough Animal Planet
for one lifetime.

39
00:03:25.289 --> 00:03:27.208
Yeah, let's head out! Come on.
The best is yet to come!

40
00:03:28.959 --> 00:03:31.712
EVAN: Gentlemen,
I have saved the best for last.

41
00:03:31.796 --> 00:03:35.341
Look over to the right.
That is your new home.

42
00:03:42.723 --> 00:03:43.891
JORDAN: That's our house?

43
00:03:43.974 --> 00:03:46.060
JOAN: I don't remember it being this big
in the brochure.

44
00:03:46.143 --> 00:03:47.395
Was it this big in the brochure?

45
00:03:47.478 --> 00:03:48.729
EVAN: Pretty amazing, isn't it?

46
00:03:48.813 --> 00:03:50.398
There they are!

47
00:03:51.649 --> 00:03:54.068
Is this curb appeal or what?

48
00:03:54.151 --> 00:03:55.653
Here we go!

49
00:03:55.736 --> 00:03:58.364
- Honey, I think you're blocking my photo.
- Sorry.

50
00:03:58.447 --> 00:04:00.408
All right, everybody! Say "escrow"!

51
00:04:00.491 --> 00:04:03.327
- Escrow!
- Escrow!

52
00:04:03.536 --> 00:04:06.163
RYAN: Come on. Come on. Come on.
Come on. Go. Go. Go.

53
00:04:06.789 --> 00:04:08.707
EVAN: Guys, easy.

54
00:04:09.125 --> 00:04:10.626
(CHILDREN EXCLAIMING)

55
00:04:11.210 --> 00:04:13.003
This is our house?

56
00:04:14.296 --> 00:04:15.464
MAN: Careful!

57
00:04:15.548 --> 00:04:17.425
JOAN: Honey, be careful!
EVAN: Watch it!

58
00:04:17.508 --> 00:04:18.634
Are you kidding me?

59
00:04:18.717 --> 00:04:19.927
- Mom, can we go upstairs?
- JOAN: Yep.

60
00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:21.429
- And I get my own room, right?
- Yep.

61
00:04:21.512 --> 00:04:22.888
(YELLING EXCITEDLY)

62
00:04:22.972 --> 00:04:25.516
Mr. Baxter, could you give us some
direction on these kitchen cabinets?

63
00:04:25.599 --> 00:04:26.600
Sure.

64
00:04:26.684 --> 00:04:31.021
Okay, it's between your maple
and your old-growth Brazilian cherry.

65
00:04:31.105 --> 00:04:33.149
That is nice! Which is best?

66
00:04:33.232 --> 00:04:36.277
Well, if you're not sensitive to that
"save the rainforest" stuff,

67
00:04:36.360 --> 00:04:37.862
you can't beat the Brazilian cherry.

68
00:04:37.945 --> 00:04:39.071
It's 200,300 years old.

69
00:04:39.155 --> 00:04:40.656
- Three hundred years.
- Three hundred.

70
00:04:40.739 --> 00:04:42.283
Wow. That is old.

71
00:04:42.366 --> 00:04:44.618
And now you are going to hold my dishes.

72
00:04:44.702 --> 00:04:46.454
- That's right. You going with the cherry?
- Cheery cherry!

73
00:04:46.537 --> 00:04:47.913
- Yeah. Definitely.
- He's going with the cherry!

74
00:04:49.248 --> 00:04:51.500
- RYAN: Dad, look!
- No, no, no!

75
00:04:51.584 --> 00:04:53.878
Ryan, do not touch him, please!

76
00:04:54.295 --> 00:04:55.838
Oh, no, no, no, no, get him away!

77
00:04:55.921 --> 00:04:58.174
No. He might have lice, fleas, maggots
or something.

78
00:04:58.257 --> 00:05:01.010
You do not play with stray dogs
because they are very...

79
00:05:01.093 --> 00:05:03.429
No, no! Get away, get away! Go!

80
00:05:04.054 --> 00:05:05.598
Okay. Oh, no, no, no.

81
00:05:05.681 --> 00:05:07.099
- He's thirsty.
- No, no, no.

82
00:05:07.183 --> 00:05:10.060
No, you don't! There we go.

83
00:05:10.144 --> 00:05:11.604
Well, Ryan, he's a stray.

84
00:05:11.687 --> 00:05:13.314
If we give him water,
he's just going to come back.

85
00:05:13.397 --> 00:05:16.775
Come on, Dad, why can't we keep him?
I mean, we've got a new house.

86
00:05:16.859 --> 00:05:18.819
Okay, Ryan, this is why we can't keep him.

87
00:05:18.903 --> 00:05:21.530
They are stinky. They are smelly.
They get hair all over the place.

88
00:05:21.614 --> 00:05:22.740
They get a little thing called the mange.

89
00:05:22.823 --> 00:05:25.868
In a nutshell, he is disgusting.
Case in point.

90
00:05:26.577 --> 00:05:28.412
(BOTH GIGGLING)

91
00:05:30.915 --> 00:05:35.836
<i>EVAN: Ladies and gentlemen, this concludes
day one of the Baxters' new and exciting life.</i>

92
00:05:35.920 --> 00:05:38.214
I have to do the new house dance.

93
00:05:38.297 --> 00:05:40.841
Wow! That dance?

94
00:05:40.925 --> 00:05:43.761
- That's a good new house dance.
- Thank you.

95
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:46.013
You know, those boys were having
so much fun tonight,

96
00:05:46.096 --> 00:05:47.932
I thought I would never get them to bed.

97
00:05:48.015 --> 00:05:52.686
And then Ryan did the cutest thing.
He asked if we could all pray together.

98
00:05:53.145 --> 00:05:55.856
Really? What did you pray about?

99
00:05:55.940 --> 00:05:58.025
He met a dog.
What do you think he prayed for?

100
00:05:58.108 --> 00:05:59.985
(EXCLAIMING IN DISGUST)

101
00:06:00.069 --> 00:06:02.821
Just a walking petri dish, that dog.

102
00:06:02.905 --> 00:06:05.074
And Jordan was very precise.

103
00:06:05.157 --> 00:06:08.953
He prayed for good visibility, good weather
on the hiking trip tomorrow.

104
00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:12.289
The hiking trip? Oh, right. Yeah.
The hiking trip. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

105
00:06:12.373 --> 00:06:14.250
You wanna know what I prayed for?

106
00:06:14.333 --> 00:06:16.210
Yeah. What did you pray for?

107
00:06:16.293 --> 00:06:19.421
I prayed we would become closer
as a family.

108
00:06:20.589 --> 00:06:25.010
Honey, you don't need to pray for that
to happen. I will make that happen.

109
00:06:25.135 --> 00:06:26.136
(SIGHING)

110
00:06:26.595 --> 00:06:30.933
- What would you pray for?
- Me? I don't know. Praying just...

111
00:06:31.684 --> 00:06:32.726
(SIGHING)

112
00:06:32.810 --> 00:06:36.647
Honey, you're the one who said
you wanted to change the world.

113
00:06:37.147 --> 00:06:39.066
It's a pretty big job.

114
00:06:39.358 --> 00:06:42.152
If it were me,
I would take all the help I could get.

115
00:06:47.157 --> 00:06:50.202
<i>WOMAN OVER TV: Former Buffalo News
anchor, Evan Baxter, takes office tomorrow</i>

116
00:06:50.286 --> 00:06:52.705
<i>to make good on a lofty campaign promise.</i>

117
00:06:52.788 --> 00:06:55.249
<i>- What are we going to do?
- ALL: Change the world!</i>

118
00:06:55.332 --> 00:06:58.794
<i>WOMAN OVER TV: Good luck, Congressman.
Many have tried, many have failed.</i>

119
00:06:58.877 --> 00:07:02.047
<i>- Hello!
- This is Regina Sparks reporting for...</i>

120
00:07:05.384 --> 00:07:06.969
(SIGHING)

121
00:07:18.355 --> 00:07:19.398
(CLEARING THROAT)

122
00:07:19.481 --> 00:07:21.317
Hello, there. Hi.

123
00:07:22.401 --> 00:07:24.737
This is Evan Baxter.

124
00:07:26.322 --> 00:07:28.782
Just wanted to say thank you for everything.

125
00:07:28.866 --> 00:07:32.661
Thank you for the new car
and for the house.

126
00:07:32.745 --> 00:07:35.706
The house is great. I love it.

127
00:07:36.373 --> 00:07:40.794
I mean, I picked it out,
but you created matter and everything, so...

128
00:07:44.298 --> 00:07:48.093
I just wanted to say that I think Joan
makes a good point,

129
00:07:48.177 --> 00:07:52.598
and that I am now in a position
of great power,

130
00:07:52.765 --> 00:07:56.644
and I know that with great power
comes great responsibility.

131
00:07:58.771 --> 00:08:00.773
So, God,

132
00:08:01.023 --> 00:08:02.024
(CLEARING THROAT)

133
00:08:04.777 --> 00:08:07.237
Please help me change the world.

134
00:08:09.156 --> 00:08:11.992
Okay. That's it. I'm hanging up now.

135
00:08:12.910 --> 00:08:15.412
God bless... Well, you. Okay.

136
00:08:31.637 --> 00:08:33.389
(ALARM RINGING)

137
00:08:38.394 --> 00:08:41.647
- What? That's weird.
- What?

138
00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:43.732
I set the alarm for 7:00.

139
00:08:46.819 --> 00:08:47.820
(MOTOR WHIRRING)

140
00:08:49.947 --> 00:08:52.032
(GRUNTING)

141
00:08:53.367 --> 00:08:54.368
(SNEEZING)

142
00:08:54.451 --> 00:08:56.036
(GRUNTING)

143
00:09:17.516 --> 00:09:19.518
I am successful. I am powerful.
I am handsome.

144
00:09:19.601 --> 00:09:22.813
I am happy, successful, powerful,
handsome, happy.

145
00:09:23.355 --> 00:09:28.402
All right, everyone, wish me luck.
The Congressman has left the building.

146
00:09:28.485 --> 00:09:33.532
All right, Baxter brood, I will see you
later on this afternoon for the big hike. Yes?

147
00:09:33.615 --> 00:09:35.909
EVAN: You psyched? Are you ready?
ALL: Yeah.

148
00:09:35.993 --> 00:09:37.244
- Bye. See you.
- Good luck, honey.

149
00:09:37.327 --> 00:09:38.454
- Bye, guys!
- See you later.

150
00:09:38.537 --> 00:09:39.538
Later, gator.

151
00:09:40.497 --> 00:09:41.498
(EXCLAIMING)

152
00:09:41.582 --> 00:09:42.875
Oh, gosh.

153
00:09:42.958 --> 00:09:45.669
Wow. Honey, did you order anything?

154
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:48.172
"Alpha and Omega Hardware"?

155
00:09:48.255 --> 00:09:50.674
- JOAN: Never heard of them.
- Me either.

156
00:09:51.008 --> 00:09:52.843
What do we have?

157
00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:54.261
(GASPING)

158
00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:56.054
What is this stuff?

159
00:09:57.473 --> 00:09:59.308
Must have the wrong address.

160
00:09:59.933 --> 00:10:01.727
Yup. The wrong address.

161
00:10:03.979 --> 00:10:05.564
WOMAN: Congressman Baxter.
Good morning.

162
00:10:05.647 --> 00:10:06.607
Good morning.

163
00:10:06.690 --> 00:10:08.025
- MAN 1: Good morning, Congressman Baxter.
- Hello.

164
00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:10.527
- MAN 2: Good morning, Congressman Baxter.
- Good morning.

165
00:10:10.611 --> 00:10:13.614
Oh, this is so cool.

166
00:10:16.825 --> 00:10:18.619
Yeah. This'll work.

167
00:10:18.702 --> 00:10:22.539
There he is! The head honcho.
The big kahuna.

168
00:10:22.623 --> 00:10:24.625
Rita, I think I have to do the dance.

169
00:10:24.708 --> 00:10:25.876
Do the dance.

170
00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:27.377
(GRUNTING)

171
00:10:29.463 --> 00:10:30.798
That's enough of the dance.

172
00:10:30.881 --> 00:10:32.966
Oh, this is nice! This is really nice!

173
00:10:33.050 --> 00:10:35.719
This is too nice.
There's something crooked going on.

174
00:10:35.803 --> 00:10:37.012
Do you smell anthrax?

175
00:10:37.095 --> 00:10:38.972
- Congressman!
- Hey, Marty!

176
00:10:39.056 --> 00:10:40.474
- Nice sound to that.
- I like it.

177
00:10:40.557 --> 00:10:41.558
Here they are!

178
00:10:41.642 --> 00:10:42.643
(ALL CHEERING)

179
00:10:42.726 --> 00:10:43.811
All right.

180
00:10:43.894 --> 00:10:45.646
You remember Sarah, Allen, Michael.

181
00:10:45.729 --> 00:10:48.398
I don't think you know the new kid
Eugene Tennanbaum. I found him at G.W.

182
00:10:48.482 --> 00:10:50.150
Sort of a walking search engine. Watch this.

183
00:10:50.234 --> 00:10:52.486
- How many stars on the flag in 1818?
- 15.

184
00:10:52.569 --> 00:10:54.488
And Congressman Baxter's coffee habits?

185
00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:57.825
He likes a morning latte with a cruller,
a decaf espresso after lunch,

186
00:10:57.908 --> 00:10:59.493
served sans pastry of any kind.

187
00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:02.246
Very impressive.
A little freaky, but I like this kid.

188
00:11:02.538 --> 00:11:03.914
(LAUGHING) I love you.

189
00:11:06.416 --> 00:11:09.753
I mean, we should hang out socially.
I just got a ping-pong table.

190
00:11:09.837 --> 00:11:11.505
Not going to happen.

191
00:11:11.588 --> 00:11:14.842
Go find out where his license plates are.
Everybody else, back to your holes.

192
00:11:14.925 --> 00:11:17.803
- EUGENE: He was actually right.
- I'm doing a background check on that kid.

193
00:11:17.886 --> 00:11:22.558
Ta-da! This, my friend, is a power office,
to remind you of the mission!

194
00:11:22.641 --> 00:11:24.059
BOTH: "Change the world!"

195
00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:25.853
- Okay, Evan, who do you know?
- What do you mean?

196
00:11:25.936 --> 00:11:27.855
Oh, come on.
Yesterday we're in the basement.

197
00:11:27.938 --> 00:11:29.857
Today, look at this place.
It's like the Emerald City!

198
00:11:29.940 --> 00:11:33.193
"Enjoy your office.
Your neighbor, Congressman Long."

199
00:11:33.277 --> 00:11:35.362
Congressman Long did this?
Did you say "neighbor"?

200
00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:38.282
That's right. He lives in Prestige Crest,
right up the street.

201
00:11:38.365 --> 00:11:42.327
Evan, you got to tell me these things.
Think of the publicity angle on this!

202
00:11:42.411 --> 00:11:44.705
You and Congressman Long having
a barbecue.

203
00:11:44.788 --> 00:11:46.665
Congressman Long eating your hot dog.

204
00:11:46.748 --> 00:11:48.458
RITA: Hate to break up
your little weenie roast.

205
00:11:48.542 --> 00:11:51.211
Congressman Long's assistant
just dropped this off.

206
00:11:51.295 --> 00:11:52.671
The Congressman would like for you

207
00:11:52.754 --> 00:11:54.923
to junior cosponsor this bill
that he's introducing.

208
00:11:55.007 --> 00:11:59.219
Hold on. Congressman Long asked us to
junior cosponsor his bill? What's the bill?

209
00:11:59.303 --> 00:12:01.972
The Citizens' Integration
of Public Lands Act.

210
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:04.057
Never heard of it. Gene, here, now.

211
00:12:04.141 --> 00:12:06.393
- Rita, why didn't you tell me about this?
- I just did.

212
00:12:06.476 --> 00:12:08.312
You need to tell me about it
before I need to know about it.

213
00:12:08.395 --> 00:12:10.522
- Marty, you are not the vice congressman.
- I am the legislative...

214
00:12:10.606 --> 00:12:14.234
Nobody voted for you. If Evan gets shot
in the head, you do not automatically...

215
00:12:14.318 --> 00:12:16.320
If Evan got shot in the head,
you're the first suspect.

216
00:12:16.403 --> 00:12:17.446
Play nice. Play nice.

217
00:12:17.529 --> 00:12:19.615
All right, Eugene, Congressman Long's bill.
What is it?

218
00:12:19.698 --> 00:12:22.576
HR71 24, better known as CINPLAN.

219
00:12:22.659 --> 00:12:25.329
The bill would open up fringe areas
of the national parks for development.

220
00:12:25.412 --> 00:12:26.914
Long's been sitting on it for ages...

221
00:12:26.997 --> 00:12:28.957
Got it. Pause. Come on, Evan, this is huge.

222
00:12:29.041 --> 00:12:30.542
You hitch your wagon to the right star,

223
00:12:30.626 --> 00:12:32.753
you could ride all the way down
to Pennsylvania Avenue.

224
00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:34.171
This is day one.

225
00:12:34.254 --> 00:12:36.423
You got your name on a major piece
of legislation!

226
00:12:36.506 --> 00:12:39.343
And another thing,
he wants you to read it today.

227
00:12:39.635 --> 00:12:41.136
Well, I can't do it today.

228
00:12:41.219 --> 00:12:42.304
- I promised my kids...
- Eugene.

229
00:12:42.387 --> 00:12:44.431
Well, sir, there's a time clock on the bill.

230
00:12:44.514 --> 00:12:46.600
If Congressman Long wants to pass it
this quarter,

231
00:12:46.683 --> 00:12:48.810
he's going to have to introduce it
to the committee immediately.

232
00:12:48.894 --> 00:12:51.396
I'm personally going with
whatever Congressman Baxter decides,

233
00:12:51.480 --> 00:12:54.441
because if I could be like one man,
it'd be him.

234
00:12:54.524 --> 00:12:55.859
Either him or Kareem.

235
00:12:55.943 --> 00:12:58.195
