and you say we're going to have a flood?

960
00:54:48.703 --> 00:54:52.206
- When might we expect this?
- September 22, midday.

961
00:54:52.290 --> 00:54:53.291
(CROWD CHATTERING)

962
00:54:56.127 --> 00:54:59.714
- That's what I was told.
- Might I ask who told you?

963
00:55:06.554 --> 00:55:10.183
Not in front of all those people.
Don't say it. Don't say it.

964
00:55:15.480 --> 00:55:16.814
God.

965
00:55:17.440 --> 00:55:18.441
(SOBBING)

966
00:55:21.611 --> 00:55:26.324
- God? You talk to God?
- Yes.

967
00:55:26.407 --> 00:55:31.078
- LONG: And God is talking back?
- Yeah. We hung out a little.

968
00:55:31.454 --> 00:55:33.748
Well, time to update the rsum.

969
00:55:33.831 --> 00:55:36.209
Congressman, your name is being removed
from this bill.

970
00:55:36.292 --> 00:55:39.712
Obviously, the stresses of this office
have proven too much for you.

971
00:55:39.795 --> 00:55:43.090
- Please have the congressman removed.
- No. Please! You don't understand!

972
00:55:43.174 --> 00:55:45.968
God commanded me to build an ark!

973
00:55:46.052 --> 00:55:48.638
It's going to rain!
There's going to be a flood!

974
00:55:50.097 --> 00:55:54.060
- Remove him now!
- We have to prepare ourselves!

975
00:55:54.143 --> 00:55:56.854
I need to finish the ark!

976
00:55:56.938 --> 00:55:57.980
(HAMMER SLAMMING)

977
00:55:58.064 --> 00:56:00.399
Remove him now!

978
00:56:06.656 --> 00:56:09.283
Does this mean we're moving back home?

979
00:56:09.575 --> 00:56:12.328
Home, Canada. One or the other.

980
00:56:22.797 --> 00:56:27.677
Joan? I know you probably saw
what happened, but I can explain.

981
00:56:31.931 --> 00:56:35.309
Take the stuff to the car, guys.
I'll be there in a minute.

982
00:56:37.562 --> 00:56:38.688
Guys?

983
00:56:40.356 --> 00:56:41.357
(DOOR OPENING)

984
00:56:42.275 --> 00:56:47.321
I'm gonna take them to my mother's.
Evan, I think you need help.

985
00:56:47.905 --> 00:56:52.702
Joan, please. I'm not doing this.
It's not me. It's him.

986
00:56:52.785 --> 00:56:56.080
I went to that meeting in a suit,
and he took it off of me.

987
00:56:56.163 --> 00:56:59.917
Those animals are following me
because of him.

988
00:57:00.001 --> 00:57:03.629
God?
Does God know he's destroying our lives?

989
00:57:03.713 --> 00:57:06.257
Does God know
he's going to get you fired?

990
00:57:06.340 --> 00:57:08.843
Yeah! He's trying to get me fired!

991
00:57:08.926 --> 00:57:12.054
He is trying to get me fired!

992
00:57:12.138 --> 00:57:14.307
That way I'll have more time
to work on the ark!

993
00:57:14.390 --> 00:57:16.892
Because the rain
and the floods are coming.

994
00:57:16.976 --> 00:57:20.396
No, I heard you, Evan.
The whole world heard you.

995
00:57:20.479 --> 00:57:23.107
Joan, please, you gotta believe me.

996
00:57:23.190 --> 00:57:24.358
(DRIZZLING)

997
00:57:25.568 --> 00:57:30.364
There it is! It's happening!
It's happening! It's raining!

998
00:57:47.882 --> 00:57:49.383
Goodbye, Evan.

999
00:57:51.010 --> 00:57:52.011
(ENGINE STARTING)

1000
00:57:52.720 --> 00:57:53.846
Joan!

1001
00:58:02.605 --> 00:58:07.193
I know! I know. Whatever you do,
you do because you love me!

1002
00:58:14.950 --> 00:58:17.787
Do me a favor. Love me less.

1003
00:58:19.163 --> 00:58:20.206
REPORTER: Congressman!

1004
00:58:20.289 --> 00:58:23.250
WOMAN: Are you concerned at all
about Congressman Baxter's tirade

1005
00:58:23.334 --> 00:58:25.002
and the adverse effects it may have
on your bill?

1006
00:58:25.086 --> 00:58:28.839
The day it rains and floods and
Congressman Baxter takes a ride on his ark,

1007
00:58:28.923 --> 00:58:30.925
that'll be the day I'll be concerned.
Thank you.

1008
00:58:31.008 --> 00:58:33.469
<i>(WAITING ON THE WORLD
TO CHANGE</i> PLAYING)

1009
00:58:34.929 --> 00:58:35.930
(BLEATING)

1010
00:58:36.013 --> 00:58:40.351
His name is Evan Baxter,
but now he goes by "New York's Noah,"

1011
00:58:40.434 --> 00:58:44.105
"Heaven's Evan,"
"The Weirdo with a Beardo."

1012
00:58:49.110 --> 00:58:52.780
Okay, guys. Watch it. Watch it.
Coming through. Watch your back.

1013
00:58:54.323 --> 00:58:58.119
Marty, will you comment on Congressman
Baxter's change of appearance?

1014
00:58:58.369 --> 00:59:02.206
Yes, his hair is long.
Yes, his beard is unshaven.

1015
00:59:02.289 --> 00:59:04.500
Are you equally stunned
by this man's appearance?

1016
00:59:10.923 --> 00:59:12.091
The way things go around here,

1017
00:59:12.174 --> 00:59:14.969
if he gets any crazier,
we may end up in the White House.

1018
00:59:15.302 --> 00:59:20.891
(REPORTER SPEAKING SPANISH)

1019
00:59:21.308 --> 00:59:23.978
Hey! No, no, no! That's my cup!

1020
00:59:25.521 --> 00:59:26.856
Whatever.

1021
00:59:47.668 --> 00:59:51.130
<i>He's filling the boat
with two of every kind of animal.</i>

1022
00:59:51.213 --> 00:59:54.508
<i>Still to be collected,
two giraffes, two elephants</i>

1023
00:59:55.634 --> 00:59:57.470
<i>and one more jackass.</i>

1024
01:00:00.681 --> 01:00:03.142
- What an idiot.
- He's a mook.

1025
01:00:03.225 --> 01:00:04.643
Jerks.

1026
01:00:05.394 --> 01:00:08.022
Don't worry about it, you guys.
Come on, eat up.

1027
01:00:08.105 --> 01:00:10.357
- Not hungry.
- Yeah, me neither.

1028
01:00:10.441 --> 01:00:12.735
You guys can't eat. I can't stop.

1029
01:00:12.818 --> 01:00:14.737
- Can I go to the bathroom?
- Me, too?

1030
01:00:14.820 --> 01:00:18.699
- Okay. Dylan, go with them. Please?
- Fine.

1031
01:00:21.410 --> 01:00:25.039
- Excuse me. Can I get a refill, please?
- Coming right up.

1032
01:00:26.123 --> 01:00:27.124
Thank you.

1033
01:00:27.208 --> 01:00:30.336
- Excuse me. Are you all right?
- Yeah.

1034
01:00:32.630 --> 01:00:36.050
- No. It's a long story.
- Well, I like stories.

1035
01:00:36.967 --> 01:00:40.012
I'm considered a bit of a storyteller myself.

1036
01:00:41.055 --> 01:00:44.183
My husband...
Have you heard of "New York's Noah"?

1037
01:00:45.768 --> 01:00:48.854
- The guy who's building the ark.
- That's him.

1038
01:00:48.938 --> 01:00:52.066
I love that story, Noah and the Ark.

1039
01:00:52.149 --> 01:00:53.734
You know, a lot of people miss the point
of that story.

1040
01:00:53.818 --> 01:00:56.403
They think it's about God's wrath and anger.

1041
01:00:56.737 --> 01:01:01.033
- They love it when God gets angry.
- What is the story about, then? The ark?

1042
01:01:01.116 --> 01:01:06.497
Well, I think it's a love story
about believing in each other.

1043
01:01:06.580 --> 01:01:12.294
You know, the animals showed up in pairs.
They stood by each other, side by side,

1044
01:01:12.378 --> 01:01:16.674
just like Noah and his family.
Everybody entered the ark side by side.

1045
01:01:17.758 --> 01:01:20.636
But my husband says God told him to do it.

1046
01:01:22.429 --> 01:01:25.933
- What do you do with that?
- Sounds like an opportunity.

1047
01:01:28.936 --> 01:01:31.188
Let me ask you something.

1048
01:01:31.272 --> 01:01:35.025
If someone prays for patience,
you think God gives them patience?

1049
01:01:35.109 --> 01:01:38.404
Or does he give them
the opportunity to be patient?

1050
01:01:40.114 --> 01:01:42.116
If they pray for courage,
does God give them courage,

1051
01:01:42.199 --> 01:01:45.536
or does he give them opportunities
to be courageous?

1052
01:01:46.996 --> 01:01:50.541
If someone prayed
for their family to be closer,

1053
01:01:50.624 --> 01:01:54.336
you think God zaps them
with warm, fuzzy feelings?

1054
01:01:54.420 --> 01:01:57.882
Or does he give them opportunities
to love each other?

1055
01:01:58.799 --> 01:01:59.967
(GASPS QUIETLY)

1056
01:02:00.050 --> 01:02:04.138
Well, I got to run.
A lot of people to serve. Enjoy.

1057
01:02:11.145 --> 01:02:14.189
<i>JON: Guess this comes as no surprise to
those who remember his campaign promise,</i>

1058
01:02:14.273 --> 01:02:16.025
<i>"I will lower taxes,</i>

1059
01:02:16.483 --> 01:02:18.652
<i>"go crazy and build a gigantic ark."</i>

1060
01:02:18.777 --> 01:02:19.778
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1061
01:02:26.702 --> 01:02:28.704
JOAN: Oh, my gosh.

1062
01:02:33.542 --> 01:02:35.586
- JOAN: Evan!
- Dad?

1063
01:02:35.669 --> 01:02:37.796
- Honey!
- Dad?

1064
01:02:37.880 --> 01:02:40.049
You guys, I'm up here.

1065
01:02:55.356 --> 01:02:56.357
(LAUGHING)

1066
01:02:56.815 --> 01:02:58.817
- Rough week?
- JORDAN: You look really funny.

1067
01:02:58.901 --> 01:03:02.237
- You look really old.
- Yeah, well, he is really old.

1068
01:03:03.989 --> 01:03:06.533
- Why'd you come back?
- It was the kids.

1069
01:03:06.617 --> 01:03:09.620
- Tell him, guys.
- We like you better as the crazy guy.

1070
01:03:09.703 --> 01:03:12.039
You spend time with us
and you're home a lot more.

1071
01:03:12.122 --> 01:03:15.250
Just, please don't make us do
the dance anymore.

1072
01:03:32.226 --> 01:03:33.227
(SIGHING)

1073
01:03:36.355 --> 01:03:40.818
I don't know what's going on,
or what you're going through,

1074
01:03:41.568 --> 01:03:47.241
but we got into this as a family
and we're gonna get out of it as a family,

1075
01:03:48.158 --> 01:03:49.827
side by side.

1076
01:03:57.251 --> 01:04:00.671
But, Evan, we have to talk about the ark.
It has to come down.

1077
01:04:00.754 --> 01:04:03.632
- I can't do that.
- You don't have a choice.

1078
01:04:04.008 --> 01:04:07.428
JOAN: Congressman Long went to the city.
There's a laundry list of code violations.

1079
01:04:07.594 --> 01:04:10.014
You have until September 22
to take it down,

1080
01:04:10.097 --> 01:04:12.016
or they'll take it down and arrest you.

1081
01:04:12.099 --> 01:04:15.602
- September 22. That's the day of the flood.
- Mom! Dad! Come here!

1082
01:04:21.984 --> 01:04:24.278
(ANIMALS CALLING)

1083
01:04:40.753 --> 01:04:43.213
Don't you dare take that ark down.

1084
01:04:45.799 --> 01:04:47.676
How are we gonna do this?

1085
01:04:47.760 --> 01:04:50.012
There's no way the five
of us can finish on time.

1086
01:04:50.095 --> 01:04:52.139
We don't have money to hire anybody else.

1087
01:04:52.222 --> 01:04:53.474
(ALPACA CRYING)

1088
01:04:57.269 --> 01:04:59.229
Is that a llama with a hammer?

1089
01:04:59.313 --> 01:05:03.400
An alpaca. They rarely spit at people
unless frightened or abused.

1090
01:05:05.235 --> 01:05:07.196
Let's finish this sucker.

1091
01:05:08.614 --> 01:05:09.615
<i>(READYFOR A MIRACLE</i> PLAYING)

1092
01:05:10.657 --> 01:05:11.700
(ELEPHANT TRUMPETING)

1093
01:05:11.784 --> 01:05:12.910
Come on, let's go.

1094
01:05:12.993 --> 01:05:14.411
<i>WOMAN:
No one knows where they came from</i>

1095
01:05:14.495 --> 01:05:16.288
<i>or how the congressman is getting them
to do it,</i>

1096
01:05:16.371 --> 01:05:22.252
<i>but, two by two, animals of all kinds
are working with Godspeed to build this ark.</i>

1097
01:05:22.336 --> 01:05:23.837
Thank you.

1098
01:05:23.921 --> 01:05:27.132
If this flood really does happen,
"Evan help us."

1099
01:05:28.759 --> 01:05:30.511
Hey! A little help?

1100
01:05:34.264 --> 01:05:35.307
Thanks.

1101
01:05:36.683 --> 01:05:37.684
JOAN: Here it is, hon.

1102
01:05:38.018 --> 01:05:39.019
(MONKEY GIBBERING)

1103
01:05:39.103 --> 01:05:41.855
Perfect. Thanks.

1104
01:05:45.734 --> 01:05:47.236
Hold it right there.

1105
01:05:47.319 --> 01:05:50.906
This is Ed Carson coming to you live
from New York Noah's construction site,

1106
01:05:50.989 --> 01:05:56.078
where we are unable to leave the news van
due to hazardous conditions outside.

1107
01:05:59.206 --> 01:06:00.207
- High five.
- High five.

1108
01:06:00.290 --> 01:06:01.291
Good job.

1109
01:06:01.959 --> 01:06:03.669
Hey, putty tat.

1110
01:06:05.963 --> 01:06:07.631
(SHRIEKING)

1111
01:06:07.714 --> 01:06:10.551
Go, go, go! He tried to eat me!

1112
01:06:10.843 --> 01:06:13.554
Dylan! Jordan! Check it out!
Your mom's building an ark!

1113
01:06:13.637 --> 01:06:14.972
Let's do the dance.

1114
01:06:15.055 --> 01:06:17.057
JOAN: No, please, no.

1115
01:06:18.642 --> 01:06:19.643
(HONKING)

1116
01:06:19.726 --> 01:06:21.645
WOMAN 1: Well, where did
the animals come from, then?

1117
01:06:21.728 --> 01:06:24.314
WOMAN 2: Please. It's a trick.
WOMAN 3: It's a circus is what it is.

1118
01:06:24.398 --> 01:06:27.484
Wild animals running amok
in suburban Virginia.

1119
01:06:27.568 --> 01:06:31.405
With all these species,
what's being done about the feces?

1120
01:06:37.411 --> 01:06:42.666
Evan Baxter! You have gone from newsman
to congressman to caveman.

1121
01:06:42.749 --> 01:06:45.544
What makes you so sure God chose you?

1122
01:06:46.503 --> 01:06:48.255
He chose all of us.

1123
01:06:57.681 --> 01:06:59.558
Time to wash up, you guys.

1124
01:07:06.148 --> 01:07:07.357
Thanks.

1125
01:07:10.777 --> 01:07:12.279
You want some?

1126
01:07:32.507 --> 01:07:35.636
RITA: Why couldn't
the man just buy a Corvette?

1127
01:07:35.719 --> 01:07:39.932
Well, well, well. There they are.
It is good to see you guys.

1128
01:07:40.015 --> 01:07:45.062
It's good to see you! Your hair looks great.
It's very regal. Man, I love your hair!

1129
01:07:45.145 --> 01:07:46.730
And you're still sucking up.

1130
01:07:46.813 --> 01:07:48.857
- So, why are you here?
- Long locked us out.

1131
01:07:48.941 --> 01:07:49.942
He can't do that.

1132
01:07:50.025 --> 01:07:52.236
I mean, I've been suspended,
but I'm still a congressman.

1133
01:07:52.319 --> 01:07:54.571
- Rita, tell him what you know.
- Tell me what?

1134
01:07:54.655 --> 01:07:57.407
I smelled a rat
the second we got that office.

1135
01:07:57.491 --> 01:07:59.576
You don't get an office like that
for nothing.

1136
01:07:59.660 --> 01:08:03.956
- So I had the stalker here do some research.
- Okay, Eugene, talk.

1137
01:08:04.081 --> 01:08:06.291
Prestige Crest used to be federal lands,

1138
01:08:06.500 --> 01:08:09.002
but what's interesting is
how it got into private hands.

1139
01:08:09.294 --> 01:08:11.630
Congressman Long got the approval
to build a dam

1140
01:08:11.713 --> 01:08:14.633
and then passed out the surrounding lands
to a group of private investors.

1141
01:08:14.716 --> 01:08:16.051
Now, the locals fought this thing for years.

1142
01:08:16.134 --> 01:08:18.387
They said Long and his developer buddies
were cutting corners,

1143
01:08:18.470 --> 01:08:20.722
like skipping important building code
checkpoints.

1144
01:08:20.806 --> 01:08:23.892
And with the land use bill, he's gonna do
the same thing with the national parks.

1145
01:08:23.976 --> 01:08:27.646
So, you stand by and shake your pom-poms
while Long and his buddies get rich.

1146
01:08:27.729 --> 01:08:29.856
What can we do? I'm suspended.

1147
01:08:29.940 --> 01:08:33.360
Go back to the Hill and show them
that you can and will fight this bill.

1148
01:08:33.443 --> 01:08:36.405
You guys, I'm sorry. I can't do that.
I have to get back to the ark.

1149
01:08:36.488 --> 01:08:38.156
The ark? All right. Okay.

1150
01:08:38.240 --> 01:08:40.158
- God told you to build an ark?
- Yes.

1151
01:08:40.242 --> 01:08:43.287
But did he tell you to make your friends
believe in you and follow you here

1152
01:08:43.370 --> 01:08:47.582
so you can make us look stupid?
'Cause I go to church every Sunday.

1153
01:08:47.666 --> 01:08:49.918
Okay, every other Sunday.

1154
01:08:50.002 --> 01:08:53.463
I've been to church!
And that does not sound like God to me.

1155
01:08:53.547 --> 01:08:55.924
Rita, I know
that this doesn't make any sense.

1156
01:08:56.008 --> 01:08:58.677
I just want you to trust me.
You just have to have faith.

1157
01:08:58.760 --> 01:09:03.390
Evan, faith will not fight this bill.
The CINPLAN vote is today!

1158
01:09:03.473 --> 01:09:07.185
If we're going to stop this thing,
you need to get down to Capitol Hill now!

1159
01:09:07.269 --> 01:09:11.565
- Otherwise, it's impossible!
- Dad, Dad, I think it's done.

1160
01:10:10.123 --> 01:10:14.378
What in the world?
I can't even get my cat to use the litter box.

1161
01:10:55.794 --> 01:11:00.215
It's September 22, and we're all still here.

1162
01:11:00.298 --> 01:11:01.800
Awkward!

1163
01:11:01.883 --> 01:11:05.262
People! The flood is imminent!

1164
01:11:05.345 --> 01:11:10.475
- Board the ark! Save yourselves!
- MAN: Get down, you fool!

1165
01:11:10.976 --> 01:11:14.938
Listen to me! The time has come!

1166
01:11:15.021 --> 01:11:19.109
No, Captain Ahab! Your time has come!

1167
01:11:19.192 --> 01:11:20.318
(ALL LAUGHING)

1168
01:11:20.402 --> 01:11:25.115
Yeah, Baxter! The weather's 70 and sunny
with a chance of crazy!

1169
01:11:25.198 --> 01:11:26.658
(ALL GIGGLING)

1170
01:11:28.368 --> 01:11:30.454
(RUMBLING)

1171
01:11:30.537 --> 01:11:36.585
- Do you hear that? The rains are upon us!
- Dad, I don't think that's the rains.

1172
01:11:37.878 --> 01:11:39.045
(SIREN BLARING)

1173
01:11:41.006 --> 01:11:43.633
MAN: Hey, Baxter! Kiss your ark goodbye!

1174
01:11:56.229 --> 01:11:58.565
- Where is he?
- On the boat, sir.

1175
01:11:59.232 --> 01:12:01.359
Give me a minute.
Lets see if I can convince "Noah"

1176
01:12:01.443 --> 01:12:03.612
that the world doesn't have to end today.

1177
01:12:07.324 --> 01:12:10.327
I gotta hand it to you,
this is quite the show.

1178
01:12:10.410 --> 01:12:13.455
According to my source,
the show hasn't even started yet.

1179
01:12:13.538 --> 01:12:15.207
Still expecting the big flood.

1180
01:12:15.290 --> 01:12:17.542
You know, voters don't respond
to the gloom and doom stuff.

1181
01:12:17.626 --> 01:12:20.795
- They like a more positive message.
- Like the one you're sending with your bill?

1182
01:12:20.879 --> 01:12:22.839
How much did you make off of all this land?

1183
01:12:22.923 --> 01:12:26.176
You are destroying
our national parks for profit.

1184
01:12:26.259 --> 01:12:28.136
You have a problem
with somebody taking a little profit?

1185
01:12:28.220 --> 01:12:29.763
It's called business, son.

1186
01:12:29.846 --> 01:12:32.349
So if I need to get a message out there,
or get a congressman elected

1187
01:12:32.432 --> 01:12:36.478
there are people who pay for it, and yes,
those people want this bill to happen

1188
01:12:36.561 --> 01:12:40.649
and, by God, it's gonna happen.
Now you look down there.

1189
01:12:41.274 --> 01:12:43.026
Those are the wolves, son.

1190
01:12:43.109 --> 01:12:46.196
I'm gonna give you one last chance.
Take down this boat.

1191
01:12:46.279 --> 01:12:50.033
I'm giving you one last chance. Repent.

1192
01:12:51.284 --> 01:12:55.205
Such a shame. You had possibilities.

1193
01:12:55.288 --> 01:12:59.167
But you want to stop progress
to save the Earth. Go for it.

1194
01:12:59.251 --> 01:13:02.212
Good luck getting a tree
to come to the polls.

1195
01:13:07.133 --> 01:13:08.635
Take it down.

1196
01:13:15.934 --> 01:13:19.145
<i>This is a court order
approving the demolition of this boat!</i>

1197
01:13:19.229 --> 01:13:22.232
<i>Evacuate immediately!
You have three minutes!</i>

1198
01:13:24.901 --> 01:13:29.114
Honey. We have to go.
They're going to destroy the boat.

1199
01:13:29.864 --> 01:13:31.032
No.

1200
01:13:32.075 --> 01:13:33.994
It can't end this way.

1201
01:13:35.328 --> 01:13:39.332
Is it too much to ask
for a little precipitation?

1202
01:13:40.500 --> 01:13:44.254
Honey, maybe God didn't mean
a literal flood.

1203
01:13:44.337 --> 01:13:49.634
Maybe he meant a flood of knowledge
or emotion or awareness.

1204
01:13:49.718 --> 01:13:51.303
If that's true,

1205
01:13:52.220 --> 01:13:55.432
I am going to be so pissed.

1206
01:13:55.515 --> 01:13:56.766
<i>Two minutes!</i>

1207
01:13:56.850 --> 01:14:00.270
<i>Get off the boat now
or you will be removed by force.</i>

1208
01:14:00.353 --> 01:14:03.898
Evan, you did it. You built the ark.

1209
01:14:03.982 --> 01:14:06.943
- That's all you were asked to do, right?
- No.

1210
01:14:07.027 --> 01:14:11.239
There's something else.
Something's going to happen. I can feel it.

1211
01:14:11.323 --> 01:14:14.117
Yeah, what's gonna happen is
tear gas and a wrecking ball.

1212
01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:16.202
Evan, think of the kids.

1213
01:14:17.287 --> 01:14:18.705
<i>One minute!</i>

1214
01:14:20.915 --> 01:14:24.502
- Dad, whatever you say, I'm with you.
- Yeah, me, too.

1215
01:14:24.586 --> 01:14:26.671
Me, too.
But can we keep some of the animals?

1216
01:14:26.755 --> 01:14:29.007
I like the alpaca. He spits.

1217
01:14:33.511 --> 01:14:36.848
You're right. We did it. We built the boat.

1218
01:14:37.223 --> 01:14:38.224
Yeah.

1219
01:14:39.225 --> 01:14:41.645
Let's go. Let's go, guys. Come on.

1220
01:14:54.741 --> 01:14:56.451
EVAN: Well, I guess they don't want to go.

1221
01:14:56.534 --> 01:14:59.621
- It's their instinct.
- What do you mean, hon?

1222
01:14:59.704 --> 01:15:04.459
Some animals know when weather's coming.
When they feel it coming, they sit.

1223
01:15:10.298 --> 01:15:11.883
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

1224
01:15:12.592 --> 01:15:13.718
Joan!

1225
01:15:17.055 --> 01:15:18.431
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

1226
01:15:23.103 --> 01:15:25.647
<i>Okay. Time's up! We're coming in!</i>

1227
01:15:25.730 --> 01:15:28.942
Get that ball in position!
We're clearing them out!

1228
01:15:35.740 --> 01:15:37.617
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1229
01:15:39.869 --> 01:15:43.164
Is that rain? It's raining.

1230
01:15:43.248 --> 01:15:45.792
Lucky guess, Baxter. Lucky guess.

1231
01:15:47.293 --> 01:15:48.294
(THUNDER CLAPPING)

1232
01:16:02.308 --> 01:16:06.563
Looks like the drought's finally over.
Good news, eh, Congressman?

1233
01:16:06.646 --> 01:16:08.815
Yeah. Good news.

1234
01:16:11.276 --> 01:16:16.823
Everybody! Please! Get on the ark!

1235
01:16:18.825 --> 01:16:20.326
Go to the car!

1236
01:16:20.410 --> 01:16:24.497
Please! Everyone! On the ark!

1237
01:16:24.581 --> 01:16:27.917
Cover me up! Keep me dry!
Cover me up! Keep me dry!

1238
01:16:28.001 --> 01:16:32.005
Who's crazy now, huh?
Look at us all squishing!

1239
01:16:40.138 --> 01:16:42.974
- It kind of stopped raining.
- Is that it?

1240
01:16:43.057 --> 01:16:45.477
What did I tell you? It's fine. It's over.

1241
01:16:45.560 --> 01:16:47.645
Hey, Ahab! This is it?

1242
01:16:48.271 --> 01:16:50.815
Your God experiencing
a little water shortage?

1243
01:16:50.899 --> 01:16:51.941
(ALL LAUGHING)

1244
01:16:52.025 --> 01:16:55.653
It would appear Evan Baxter
was right about the rain,

1245
01:16:55.737 --> 01:16:59.240
with a slight miscalculation
as to the quantity.

1246
01:17:03.328 --> 01:17:06.539
- Something's wrong.
- Honey, the clouds are moving away.

1247
01:17:06.623 --> 01:17:09.626
No, no. No, this isn't right.

1248
01:17:10.460 --> 01:17:13.838
Evan, even if it kept raining,
it's not like it could cause a flood in a day.

1249
01:17:13.922 --> 01:17:19.177
But today is the day! It has to be.
This just doesn't make any sense!

1250
01:17:21.137 --> 01:17:23.348
- Wait a second.
- What is it?

1251
01:17:23.431 --> 01:17:27.101
Marty said that Long cut corners,
violated building codes.

1252
01:17:27.185 --> 01:17:29.729
- What are you talking about?
- The lake, Long Lake.

1253
01:17:29.813 --> 01:17:33.733
It's named after him.
It's the lake! It's the lake!

1254
01:17:46.913 --> 01:17:48.248
Oh, no.

1255
01:17:50.083 --> 01:17:54.796
Get on the ark! Everyone, on the ark now!

1256
01:17:54.879 --> 01:17:56.714
I think we should get on the ark.

1257
01:17:56.798 --> 01:17:59.634
I agree.
I think we should get on the ark also.

1258
01:17:59.717 --> 01:18:03.346
I'm cold. I'm wet. I'm going home.

1259
01:18:10.270 --> 01:18:12.438
Ladies first! Move!

1260
01:18:20.321 --> 01:18:23.950
Oh, my God. This is happening.
This is really happening.

1261
01:18:25.034 --> 01:18:28.371
Holy... Get everyone on the ark now!

1262
01:18:28.454 --> 01:18:31.082
Get on the ark now! Let's go!
Get on the ark! Let's go!

1263
01:18:31.165 --> 01:18:34.043
Go, go, go! Get on the ark!

1264
01:18:34.127 --> 01:18:35.628
(ALL SCREAMING)

1265
01:18:35.712 --> 01:18:39.841
Go, go, go! On the ark! Go, go, go!

1266
01:18:39.924 --> 01:18:42.385
All right, boys! Let's go! Let's go!

1267
01:18:42.468 --> 01:18:46.014
We're gonna need a bigger boat.
Stay here with the kids.

1268
01:18:55.148 --> 01:18:56.983
Come on, Rita!

1269
01:18:57.066 --> 01:19:01.237
Everyone, up the ramp! Onto the deck!
Come on! Hurry, hurry, hurry!

1270
01:19:01.321 --> 01:19:05.158
- Dylan, get back inside! It's too dangerous.
- No, Dad. I told you, I'm with you.

1271
01:19:09.537 --> 01:19:12.332
EVAN: Careful, everyone.
In the ark! In the ark!

1272
01:19:12.415 --> 01:19:14.500
Watch your step! Up the ramp, everybody!

1273
01:19:22.759 --> 01:19:24.719
- Guys, help me with the door!
- Get the door! Get the door!

1274
01:19:32.185 --> 01:19:34.103
(ALL SCREAMING)

1275
01:20:07.887 --> 01:20:09.430
Guys! Guys!

1276
01:20:42.422 --> 01:20:44.173
Everybody hang on!

1277
01:20:54.434 --> 01:20:55.518
(ROARING)

1278
01:20:55.601 --> 01:20:57.770
You guys all right? You okay?

1279
01:20:58.396 --> 01:20:59.939
<i>MAN OVER TV:
There's been a flood at Prestige Crest</i>

1280
01:21:00.023 --> 01:21:02.191
<i>and you're seeing live images
of New York Noah's ark</i>

1281
01:21:02.275 --> 01:21:05.486
<i>caught in the storm surge
and heading towards Memorial Bridge!</i>

1282
01:21:13.327 --> 01:21:15.872
WOMAN: We're going to crash!
MAN: Turn this thing around!

1283
01:21:15.955 --> 01:21:18.791
MAN 2: We're not gonna make it!
MAN 3: Save us, Baxter!

1284
01:21:30.511 --> 01:21:35.099
I command thee halt! Stop! Whoa!

1285
01:21:35.183 --> 01:21:36.851
WOMAN: It's not working!

1286
01:21:37.643 --> 01:21:40.396
How about a little help here?

1287
01:21:56.662 --> 01:21:57.663
(SCREAMING)

1288
01:22:24.816 --> 01:22:25.858
(SCREAMING)

1289
01:22:26.234 --> 01:22:28.736
What do you mean there was water damage?
It rained for ten minutes.

1290
01:22:28.820 --> 01:22:30.613
That is not possible.

1291
01:22:39.163 --> 01:22:40.164
(EXCLAIMING)

1292
01:22:40.248 --> 01:22:42.125
- I love you guys.
- All right.

1293
01:22:42.208 --> 01:22:43.459
- Seriously.
- Okay, I got it.

1294
01:22:43.543 --> 01:22:44.669
- I love you.
- Thank you.

1295
01:22:44.752 --> 01:22:46.045
(EAGLE CRYING)

1296
01:23:02.145 --> 01:23:06.732
LONG: All those in favor of the Public
Land Act, please signify by saying, "Aye."

1297
01:23:07.066 --> 01:23:09.026
(CLAMORING)

1298
01:23:13.823 --> 01:23:15.116
Good God!

1299
01:23:24.125 --> 01:23:25.918
(ALL YELLING)

1300
01:23:50.443 --> 01:23:51.861
I think we can walk from here.

1301
01:23:51.944 --> 01:23:53.529
(SIRENS BLARING)

1302
01:24:10.129 --> 01:24:14.759
Hello, Congressman.
Mind if I park my boat here for a little while?

1303
01:24:15.843 --> 01:24:17.929
- But how...
- The dam, Congressman.

1304
01:24:18.012 --> 01:24:21.557
Your reservoir ruptured.
Prestige Crest, it's all gone.

1305
01:24:21.641 --> 01:24:24.185
No. They said that couldn't happen.

1306
01:24:25.228 --> 01:24:26.938
I never thought this...

1307
01:24:27.813 --> 01:24:32.693
You. You did this to me.
You set me up, you crazy son of a...

1308
01:24:32.777 --> 01:24:35.947
(MONKEYS SCREECHING)

1309
01:24:36.030 --> 01:24:38.366
Wow. That is disgusting.

1310
01:24:38.824 --> 01:24:40.243
If that comes out your front,

1311
01:24:40.326 --> 01:24:43.746
I don't even want to know
what's coming out the back.

1312
01:24:45.498 --> 01:24:46.916
(SNARLING)

1313
01:24:46.999 --> 01:24:49.543
Don't look down, Congressman,
but the wolves are here,

1314
01:24:49.627 --> 01:24:53.547
although I wouldn't worry so much
about these wolves as those.

1315
01:25:01.847 --> 01:25:03.224
<i>Gesundheit.</i>

1316
01:25:15.319 --> 01:25:18.948
<i>MAN 1: As you can see behind me,
New York Noah's prediction came true.</i>

1317
01:25:19.031 --> 01:25:21.534
<i>WOMAN: The vote of the Land Act Bill
has been suspended,</i>

1318
01:25:21.617 --> 01:25:24.453
<i>pending investigation of Congressman Long
for profiteering...</i>

1319
01:25:24.537 --> 01:25:27.498
MAN 2: Of course now, the question is,
how will these animals be returned

1320
01:25:27.581 --> 01:25:29.125
to their natural habitats?

1321
01:25:29.208 --> 01:25:33.087
Something tells me, if God got them here,
he can probably get them home.

1322
01:25:33.170 --> 01:25:36.215
<i>WOMAN 2: The House will undoubtedly
reinstate Congressman Baxter</i>

1323
01:25:36.299 --> 01:25:38.050
<i>when it reconvenes in the morning.</i>

1324
01:25:38.134 --> 01:25:41.971
<i>Until then, there is a lot to be done here
on Capitol Hill.</i>

1325
01:25:42.054 --> 01:25:44.140
JORDAN: How's Buster doing?
EVAN: Come on, Buster.

1326
01:25:44.223 --> 01:25:46.600
JOAN: No, come on. Come on!
RYAN: Come on!

1327
01:25:46.684 --> 01:25:48.477
EVAN: These too heavy? It's all right?
JORDAN: No, it's fine.

1328
01:25:48.561 --> 01:25:50.980
- RYAN: He can't keep up.
- I know, sweetie!

1329
01:25:51.063 --> 01:25:54.275
All right.
What do you say we take a little break?

1330
01:25:54.358 --> 01:25:55.985
We've only been walking
for, like, five minutes, Dad.

1331
01:25:56.068 --> 01:25:59.280
Well, five on, five off.
Life is about balance, right?

1332
01:25:59.363 --> 01:26:00.656
- How about some sandwiches?
- Okay.

1333
01:26:00.740 --> 01:26:03.617
- Who wants sandwiches? Let's do it!
- RYAN: I get first dibs!

1334
01:26:03.701 --> 01:26:05.995
Everyone but Buster
is going to get a sandwich.

1335
01:26:06.078 --> 01:26:10.458
You do not get a sandwich! You're a dog
and you do not get a sandwich!

1336
01:26:10.541 --> 01:26:13.753
Buster is part of the family now.
You're just gonna have to get used to it.

1337
01:26:13.836 --> 01:26:15.671
Poor Buster!

1338
01:26:16.422 --> 01:26:19.508
Honey, come here.
Sweetheart, be careful. Come here.

1339
01:26:19.592 --> 01:26:21.510
- Hey, hon, save me one, okay?
- Okay.

1340
01:26:21.594 --> 01:26:23.346
I'll be right back.

1341
01:26:31.354 --> 01:26:32.730
- Hey.
- Hey.

1342
01:26:34.607 --> 01:26:36.567
What are you doing here?

1343
01:26:36.859 --> 01:26:39.278
Just hanging out with some old friends.

1344
01:26:39.362 --> 01:26:42.656
You knew all along, didn't you?
You knew the dam was unstable.

1345
01:26:42.740 --> 01:26:46.577
If it hadn't been for the ark,
my family, the neighbors...

1346
01:26:46.660 --> 01:26:50.456
- I fought you every step of the way.
- Yes, but you did it.

1347
01:26:51.457 --> 01:26:56.003
So, you had nothing to do with the flood?
Like where the ark landed exactly?

1348
01:26:56.087 --> 01:26:59.548
I gave you a little shove at the end. Sue me.

1349
01:26:59.632 --> 01:27:00.633
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

1350
01:27:02.134 --> 01:27:05.846
You did good, son. You changed the world.

1351
01:27:05.930 --> 01:27:08.599
- No, no, I didn't.
- Well, let's see.

1352
01:27:08.682 --> 01:27:12.770
Spending time with your family,
making them very happy.

1353
01:27:12.853 --> 01:27:16.148
- Gave that dog a home.
- Right. So?

1354
01:27:16.816 --> 01:27:18.526
So?

1355
01:27:18.609 --> 01:27:20.736
How do we change the world?

1356
01:27:22.321 --> 01:27:25.741
One act of random kindness at a time.

1357
01:27:25.825 --> 01:27:30.371
One act of random kindness.

1358
01:27:35.501 --> 01:27:36.836
It's time.

1359
01:27:38.879 --> 01:27:40.381
Do the dance.

1360
01:27:41.841 --> 01:27:43.509
Care to join me?

1361
01:27:49.390 --> 01:27:50.391
(CHUCKLING)

1362
01:28:05.489 --> 01:28:06.490
(DOVE COOING)

1363
01:28:40.024 --> 01:28:44.737
I now issue a new commandment,
"Thou shalt do the dance."

1364
01:28:44.945 --> 01:28:46.655
<i>(GONNA MAKE YOU SWEAT,
EVERYBODYDANCE NOW</i> PLAYING)

1365
01:29:40.793 --> 01:29:42.294
(LIP-SYNCING)

1366
01:29:47.049 --> 01:29:50.177
Stop it! This is stupid!

1367
01:29:50.261 --> 01:29:53.472
That's awful dancing! You better stop!

1368
01:29:59.311 --> 01:30:01.063
(LIP-SYNCING)

1369
01:30:16.996 --> 01:30:17.997
(LIP-SYNCING)

1370
01:30:26.380 --> 01:30:28.007
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

1371
01:30:31.760 --> 01:30:33.887
<i>MAN 1: Ladies and gentlemen,
you don't have to go home.</i>

1372
01:30:33.971 --> 01:30:36.599
<i>You just have to go. We are wrapped.</i>

1373
01:30:36.682 --> 01:30:39.393
<i>MAN 2: We're wrapped.
We love you. Thank you.</i>

1374
01:30:40.185 --> 01:30:42.187
<i>(READYFOR A MIRACLE</i> PLAYING)

